=head1 DESCRIPTION

The size and type of temporary storage that is used to hold data during
the savedown process. All the data written to this storage space is
lost when the cluster node is restarted.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Size => Int

The size of temporary storage in gibibytes.


=head2 Type => Str

The type of writeable storage space for temporarily storing your
savedown data. The valid values are:

=over

=item *

SDS01 E<ndash> This type represents 3000 IOPS and io2 ebs volume type.

=back



=head2 VolumeName => Str

The name of the kdb volume that you want to use as writeable save-down
storage for clusters.



